.TH HYPERCTL 1 "January 2026" "hyperctl 1.0.0" "Hypervisor SDK"
.SH NAME
hyperctl \- control CLI for hypervisord daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hyperctl
[\fB\-\-daemon\fR \fIURL\fR]
.I COMMAND
[\fIARGS\fR...]
.br
.B hyperctl
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hyperctl
is a command-line interface for managing VM export jobs through the
.B hypervisord
daemon. It provides commands for submitting jobs, querying status, and managing
the export queue.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-daemon " " \fIURL\fR
Daemon URL (default: http://localhost:8080)
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show version information
.SH COMMANDS
.SS VM Operations
.TP
.B list
List all VMs from vCenter
.TP
.B list \-json
List VMs in JSON format
.TP
.B list \-filter \fINAME\fR
Filter VMs by name pattern
.TP
.B vm \-op \fIOPERATION\fR \-path \fIPATH\fR
Perform VM operation (shutdown|poweroff|remove-cdrom|info)
.SS Job Management
.TP
.B submit \-vm \fIPATH\fR \-output \fIDIR\fR
Submit a single VM export job
.TP
.B submit \-file \fIFILE\fR
Submit jobs from YAML/JSON file
.TP
.B query \-all
Query all jobs
.TP
.B query \-id \fIID\fR
Query specific job by ID
.TP
.B query \-status \fISTATUS\fR
Query jobs by status (pending|running|completed|failed)
.TP
.B status
Show daemon status and statistics
.TP
.B cancel \-id \fIID\fR[,\fIID\fR...]
Cancel running jobs
.SS Interactive Mode
.TP
.B migrate
Launch interactive TUI for VM selection and migration
.TP
.B migrate \-output \fIDIR\fR
Set output directory for migrations
.TP
.B migrate \-convert=false
Skip automatic conversion to qcow2
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS List VMs
.PP
List all VMs:
.RS 4
hyperctl list
.RE
.PP
List in JSON format:
.RS 4
hyperctl list \-json
.RE
.PP
Filter by name:
.RS 4
hyperctl list \-filter rhel
.RE
.SS VM Operations
.PP
Graceful shutdown:
.RS 4
hyperctl vm \-op shutdown \-path /datacenter/vm/my\-vm
.RE
.PP
Force power off:
.RS 4
hyperctl vm \-op poweroff \-path /datacenter/vm/my\-vm
.RE
.PP
Remove CD/DVD devices:
.RS 4
hyperctl vm \-op remove\-cdrom \-path /datacenter/vm/my\-vm
.RE
.PP
Get VM information:
.RS 4
hyperctl vm \-op info \-path /datacenter/vm/my\-vm
.RE
.SS Job Management
.PP
Submit single VM export:
.RS 4
hyperctl submit \-vm /datacenter/vm/my\-vm \-output /tmp/export
.RE
.PP
Submit batch from file:
.RS 4
hyperctl submit \-file jobs.yaml
.RE
.PP
Query all jobs:
.RS 4
hyperctl query \-all
.RE
.PP
Query running jobs:
.RS 4
hyperctl query \-status running
.RE
.PP
Cancel a job:
.RS 4
hyperctl cancel \-id abc123
.RE
.PP
Show daemon status:
.RS 4
hyperctl status
.RE
.SS Interactive Migration
.PP
Launch interactive mode:
.RS 4
hyperctl migrate
.RE
.PP
Migrate with custom output directory:
.RS 4
hyperctl migrate \-output /migrations
.RE
.SH JOB FILE FORMAT
Job files use YAML or JSON format:
.PP
.B Single VM (job.yaml):
.RS 4
.nf
name: "vm-export-1"
vm_path: "/datacenter/vm/my-vm"
output_path: "/tmp/export"
options:
  parallel_downloads: 4
  remove_cdrom: true
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Batch (batch.yaml):
.RS 4
.nf
jobs:
  - name: "vm-1"
    vm_path: "/datacenter/vm/vm-1"
    output_path: "/tmp/export-1"
  - name: "vm-2"
    vm_path: "/datacenter/vm/vm-2"
    output_path: "/tmp/export-2"
.fi
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B DAEMON_URL
Daemon URL (default: http://localhost:8080)
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.hyperctl/config
User configuration file
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.TP
.B 2
Connection error to daemon
.TP
.B 3
Invalid arguments
